{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:04.273789+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: aafb1240db602fd1ff16225d59f74ed7c4701151)", "id": "lc_9a9e8fcf-232a-446e-9ee5-fc47fbe517af"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<template>\n  <nav class=\"navbar navbar-expand-md navbar-dark bg-dark fixed-top\">\n    <div class=\"container\">\n      <RouterLink to=\"/\" class=\"navbar-brand\" @click=\"collapseNavbar\">ProjectName</RouterLink>\n      <button\n        :class=\"['navbar-toggler', !navbarExpanded && 'collapsed']\"\n        type=\"button\"\n        aria-controls=\"navbarDefault\"\n        :aria-expanded=\"navbarExpanded\"\n        aria-label=\"Toggle navigation\"\n        @click=\"toggleNavbar\"\n      >\n        <span class=\"navbar-toggler-icon\"></span>\n      </button>\n\n      <div id=\"navbarDefault\" :class=\"['collapse navbar-collapse', navbarExpanded && 'show']\">\n        <ul class=\"navbar-nav mr-auto\">\n          <li class=\"nav-item\">\n            <RouterLink to=\"/\" class=\"nav-link\" @click=\"collapseNavbar\">Home</RouterLink>\n          </li>\n          <li class=\"nav-item\">\n            <RouterLink to=\"/about\" class=\"nav-link\" @click=\"collapseNavbar\">About</RouterLink>\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </nav>\n</template>\n\n<script setup>\nimport { ref } from 'vue'\n\ndefineOptions({\n  name: 'DefaultNav',\n})\n\nconst navbarExpanded = ref(false)\n\nconst toggleNavbar = () => {\n  navbarExpanded.value = !navbarExpanded.value\n}\n\nconst collapseNavbar = () => {\n  navbarExpanded.value = false\n}\n</script>\n", "id": "lc_9ef96bb9-6f47-420a-ae5e-acf11679b6cb"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "57ba54a9-4305-454a-ba17-3b43c21c7eb0", "tool_call_id": "call_d1b67652b6864712b0132b2f", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:32.581060+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a complete explanation of how the app bootstraps routing, layout rendering, and how the About page loads.\n\n---\n\n## App Bootstrap Flow\n\n### 1. Entry Point: `src/main.js`\n\n```js\nimport Default from '@/layouts/default/Default.vue'\nimport App from './App.vue'\nimport { router } from './router'\n\nconst app = createApp(App)\napp.component('LayoutDefault', Default)   // registers layout as a global component\napp.use(createPinia())                     // state management\napp.use(router)                            // Vue Router\napp.mount('#app')\n```\n\nKey actions:\n- Creates the Vue app instance from `App.vue`.\n- **Globally registers** the `Default.vue` layout as `LayoutDefault` — this makes it available by name in any template.\n- Installs Pinia (store) and the router.\n- Mounts to `#app` in `index.html`.\n\n### 2. Dynamic Layout Selection: `src/App.vue`\n\n```html\n<template>\n  <component :is=\"layout\">\n    <RouterView />\n  </component>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nexport default {\n  name: 'App',\n  computed: {\n    layout() {\n      return `layout-${this.$route.meta.layout || 'default'}`\n    },\n  },\n}\n</script>\n```\n\nThis is the core layout-switching mechanism:\n- A **computed property** reads `this.$route.meta.layout` (from the matched route). If not set, it defaults to `'default'`.\n- The result (e.g. `'layout-default'`) is passed to Vue's dynamic `<component :is=\"...\">`.\n- Because `LayoutDefault` was registered globally in `main.js`, Vue resolves `layout-default` → `LayoutDefault` → the `Default.vue` layout component.\n- `<RouterView />` is passed as the **default slot** content inside the layout.\n\n### 3. Router Definition: `src/router/index.js`\n\n```js\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,                          // eagerly imported\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    component: () => import('../views/About.vue'),  // lazy-loaded (code-split)\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n]\nconst router = createRouter({\n  linkActiveClass: 'active',\n  history: createWebHashHistory(),   // hash-based routing (#/about)\n  routes,\n})\n```\n\n- Uses **hash history** (`#/` URLs), so navigation works without server-side routing configuration.\n- Both routes declare `meta.layout: 'default'`, which triggers the default layout in `App.vue`.\n- The `Home` component is **eagerly imported** (bundled into the main chunk).\n- The `About` component uses a **dynamic `import()`** — this creates a separate code-split chunk that is fetched on demand.\n\n### 4. Default Layout: `src/layouts/default/Default.vue`\n\n```html\n<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />               <!-- RouterView content lands here -->\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\n- Renders a **navbar** (`DefaultNav.vue` — a dark Bootstrap navbar with Home and About links) at the top.\n- Exposes a **`<slot />`** in the middle — this is where `<RouterView />` from `App.vue` renders the matched page component.\n- Renders a **footer** (`DefaultFooter.vue`) at the bottom.\n- Includes sticky-footer CSS so the footer stays pinned to the bottom.\n\n---\n\n## How the About Page Loads (step by step)\n\n1. **User navigates** to `/#/about` (e.g., by clicking the \"About\" link in the navbar, which is a `<RouterLink to=\"/about\">`).\n\n2. **Vue Router** matches the `/about` route definition. The `meta.layout` is `'default'`.\n\n3. **`App.vue`** recomputes its `layout` computed property → `'layout-default'`, which resolves to the globally registered `LayoutDefault` component (`Default.vue`).\n\n4. **The `About` component is lazy-loaded** — the dynamic `import('../views/About.vue')` triggers a network request for a separate JavaScript chunk (named `about.[hash].js`). This is **code splitting** in action: the About page code isn't included in the initial bundle.\n\n5. **Once the chunk loads**, `About.vue` is rendered inside the `<slot />` of `Default.vue`. The final DOM structure is:\n\n```\n<div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n  <DefaultNav />          ← dark navbar with Home/About links\n  <div class=\"container\"> ← from About.vue\n    <h1>This is the about page</h1>\n  </div>\n  <DefaultFooter />       ← sticky footer\n</div>\n```\n\n6. **`DefaultNav`** highlights the \"About\" link as active (via Vue Router's `linkActiveClass: 'active'` combined with `RouterLink`'s automatic active-class behavior).\n\n---\n\n**In summary:** The app uses a convention-based dynamic layout system — routes declare their layout in `meta`, `App.vue` resolves it to a globally registered component name, and `<RouterView />` is passed as a slot. The About page specifically benefits from **route-level code splitting**, so its JavaScript is only fetched when the user first navigates to `/about`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1640, "prompt_tokens": 13776, "total_tokens": 15416, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 470, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 13312, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0016765632, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002497632, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0014268}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863184-ZhK7HgKzQtghsSz5f2hL", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b7-ad92-7c30-b2bd-37c472926b7e-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13776, "output_tokens": 1640, "total_tokens": 15416, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 13312}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 470}}}}]}}}
